Fourteen people were injured when a minibus taxi and a car collided in the Gomane area in the KwaZulu-Natal midlands on Sunday afternoon, paramedics said.
Netcare 911 responded at about 1.15pm to reports of a collision on the R617 in the Gomane region in the midlands, Netcare 911 spokesman Shawn Herbst said.
“Upon arrival, multiple ambulance services were already in attendance. Reports from the scene indicate that a light motor vehicle and a minibus taxi were involved in a collision. A total of 14 people were injured.”
All the injured were treated on the scene and transported by various services to hospital for further assessment and care. Authorities were on the scene to investigate, Herbst said.
– African News Agency (ANA)